    Title: Srimad Bhagavatam
    Locus: XI iv
Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Work, Action and Society=God the Only Doer
  - 978
---
As long as there is consciousness of diversity and not of unity in the
Self, a man ignorantly thinks of himself as a separate being, as the
‘doer’ of actions and the ‘experiencer’ of effects. He remains subject
to birth and death, knows happiness and misery, is bound by his own
deeds, good or bad.
